This paper addresses the problem of motion planning for a robotic manipulator, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes an algorithm that integrates sampling-based motion planning with a novel hierarchical search, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The task of placing an object in a cluttered environment may also involve computer vision (cs.CV) to perceive the environment and identify suitable placement poses. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of optimization techniques to optimize the placement objective, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
